Actress Mercy Aigbe’s unveiling of her new boo, Kazim Adeoti, founder of Adekaz production has continued to elicit mixed reactions on social media. In December 2021, Mercy Aigbe was rumoured to have secretly had her Nikkah with the entertainment mogul. Lanre Gentry, the former husband of the movie star reacting to the news, shared an old photo of them while they were still married alongside her new boo. In his caption, Gentry expressed gratitude to God for unveiling ‘the truth’ while accusing the mother of two of infidelity with several men. “At last I thank God the truth is out this is just one out of many to God be the glory”, he wrote.   Resist distractions, Obi Cubana counsels youths     Life would have been easier if I wasn’t gay – Temmy…     How I battled health crisis in 2021, by Ngozi Nwosu   - Advertisement - He added: “I don’t need anyone’s comment please.” Ensuring he achieved that, Gentry blocked the comment section of the post. In 2017, Aigbe parted ways after she accused him of domestic violence while he accused her of infidelity. Lanre however got married in September 2021. He tied the knot with his new bride, Oluwabusayo, in a ceremony that was attended by family, friends and fans.